My thought would be to keep the fs5 scheme of using flat tiles
at least in Flight-Gears initial release.  As far as I know, we've just been 
introduced to triangular mesh with Shiratti Commander and Hans 
Meier's Mount and designers are finally laying down 3d mountains that 
look like mountains. Once this catches on, and I think it already 
has, 3dpoly util programmers will be refining their code and maybe 
adding more bells and whistles?  This would allow you to let them 
advance this technology (code) if you need more information on going 
about this most efficiently?  I don't know how much you already know 
about this :-)    Another reason, Curt you said it would be much 
easier to allow current bgl formatted scenery to be used in F.G.  
Again, maybe this might be better taken care of after F.G is out.
It's the same approach I'm using in my scenery :-)  I'm building the
basics first, and will continue to upgrade it once I have the first 
release out.  Later will come more mountains, objects, houses, boats, 
etc.  Just my thoughts.

Getting back to triangular mesh, I'm about 1/3 done with the mountain 
portion of my scenery project and I can tell you it's slow going 
doing this manually.  I haven't used S.C to build mountains so I'm 
not sure if Enrico instilled some sort of auto generating mechanism 
or if it requires hand drawn mountains as Hans' program requires (up 
